{ Hi guys!🎉 Welcome to another study about the London System. I will show you everything about it and once you finish this study, make sure to use this opening in your own games!👍
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Before you read all of this, please check this study all about the Reti Opening: https://lichess.org/study/iN61Eams
In there, I put the all the options that black can play against it and it is a good opening to pair with the London System.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
This is the London System. These are where the pieces usually go (there are exceptions). The pawns go on c3, d4 and e3, the knights are on d2 and f3, and the bishops are on d3 and f4.

This system is good ✔ for beginner to advanced level as it doesn't have lots of theory to memorize and it is a system.🤔 The pieces are placed on these specific squares to have a simple idea: You want to attack on the kingside, if not, get a super solid structure that cannot be broken down easily.😃

One of the best tries for black is to play a Benoni, but you are prepared against that. You can either draw or win.

In section 1, I covered the main lines in the London that you can play. Those lines are what your opponent might play against you.

In section 2, I covered the patterns in the London System. Those patterns are useful to master the London System.

In section 3, I covered traps that your opponent might fall for. Those traps have happened in master games.

In section 4, I put games played by the best GMs in the world. I put those games to illustrate how masters play the London.

In section 5, I covered alternatives that are either as good or better than the main lines. You will have lots of fun in those positions and you will have very instructive games in that position.🤑

If you want, I will do a section 6 to show you how to counter the London System. Those are simple and easy to learn and don't require a lot of theory.

If you want, I will publish a section 7 where I will show you my games in the London System for both white and black to illustrate ideas for both sides. You will surely master the London System after this study and have lots of great games with it.

Don't forget to leave a like👍 on this study! Once this study reaches 3000 likes, please tell me your usernames and I will do a spin the wheel for 5 contributors that will contribute to this study.

I hope you will have fun while going into the adventure of a London System player!🎉🎉🎉🎉

Without further ado, let's get straight into action!👌 } { [%csl Bc3,Bd4,Be3,Bf2,Bf4,Bf3,Bd3,Bd2,Bb2] }
 *


