{ We start with d4. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 Nf6 { This is their most flexible option. We just play Bf4. } { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 g6 { The reason why we didn't play Nf3 is because we want to play Nc3 first which provokes them to play d5 then we will play Nf3. If they played Bg7 instead, we just play e4 and Qd2 and attack them on the kingside. } { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 3. Nc3!? { This is a small deviation from our system. We usually put the knight on d2 but we can place it on c3. e3 is also possible on the third move.
They have two moves. They can play d5 or Bg7. d5 is the main line because it controls e4, and if they play Bg7, we play e4, Qd2, 0-0-0, f3 and smash them on the kingside with h4 h5 g4 g5. } (3. e3 { This is a more positional approach so this will be covered in section 5. }) (3. Nf3 { This transposes into the 3. e3 lines so this will be covered in section 5. }) (3. Nd2 { This idea of 3. Nd2 will be covered in section 5 (trust me there is going to be fire here🔥). }) 3... d5 { We just play e3. } { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } (3... Bg7 4. e4 c5 5. Qd2 cxd4 6. Qxd4 Nh5 7. Qd2 Nxf4 8. Qxf4 Qa5 9. O-O-O) 4. e3 Bg7 { Now we play Nf3. } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 5. Nf3 { This piece placement is known as the Barry Attack. } { [%csl Bc3,Bd4,Be3,Bf3,Bf4] } 5... c5 { We now play Be2. } { [%csl Be2][%cal Bf1e2] } 6. Be2 { Notice that we don't put the bishop on d3 because it is just biting at stone because of the g6 pawn. } 6... Nc6 { Now we play Ne5. } { [%csl Be5][%cal Bf3e5] } 7. Ne5 O-O { Castle the king! } { [%csl Gg1][%cal Ge1g1] } 8. O-O cxd4 9. exd4 Qb6 { [%csl Bc6][%cal Be5c6] } 10. Nxc6 Qxc6 { [%csl Ba4][%cal Ba2a4] } 11. a4 { You want to play Bb5 and a5 to harass the queen. } 11... a6 { [%csl Ba5][%cal Ba4a5] } 12. a5 Bf5 { Attack, attack, attack!!!!!!!!!!!!! } { [%csl Rg4][%cal Rg2g4] } 13. g4 { WE ARE NOW ATTACKING!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! } 13... Be6 { [%csl Ba4][%cal Bc3a4] } 14. Na4 { We want to place the knight on c5. } { [%csl Rc5][%cal Ra4c5] } 14... Nd7 { Develop the rook to the semi-open file. } { [%csl Ye1][%cal Yf1e1] } 15. Re1 f5 { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rg4g5] } 16. g5 { You are now in the driver's seat.
--Point--
You want to castle the king, gain space on both sides of the board, and just keep attacking. } *


