{ We play d4 on the first move. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 { [%eval 0.15] } 1... f5 { [%eval 0.47] [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } (1... Nf6) 2. Bf4 { [%eval 0.37] } 2... Nf6 { [%eval 0.52] [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 3. e3 { [%eval 0.64] } 3... e6 { [%eval 0.67] [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 4. Nf3 { [%eval 0.58] } 4... Be7 { [%eval 0.55] [%csl Bh3][%cal Bh2h3] } 5. h3 { [%eval 0.61] } { We don't play this to save the bishop. We play this for a secret plan you'll see later. } 5... O-O { [%eval 1.13] [%csl Bd2][%cal Bb1d2] } 6. Nbd2 { [%eval 0.85] } 6... b6 { [%eval 1.39] [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 7. Bd3 { [%eval 0.98] } 7... Bb7 { [%eval 1.17] [%csl Bc3][%cal Bc2c3] } 8. c3 { [%eval 1.37] } { We have now completed the system. It is now time to attack! } { [%csl Bc3,Bd4,Bd3,Bd2,Be3,Bf3,Bf4,Bb2,Bf2] } 8... c5 { [%eval 1.36] } { No castling! Remember the secret idea I said earlier? Here it comes! } 9. Rg1 { [%eval 1.4] } { We now are about to play g4! You will have some fun in these positions. } 9... Ne4 { [%eval 1.67] [%csl Bg4][%cal Bg2g4] } 10. g4 { [%eval 1.69] } { We are considered to be better here in this position due to the attack.
--Point--
You want to complete the system and play h3, play Rg1, and finally, play g4 to blast open lines on the kingside. } *


