{ Let's play d4! } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 d5 { Develop the knight to f3 } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 2. Nf3 (2. Bf4) 2... Nc6 { Place the bishop on f4 } { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } (2... Nf6) 3. Bf4 Bg4 { We now play e3 } { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 4. e3 e6 { We now need to play c4! } { [%csl Bc4][%cal Bc2c4] } 5. c4! { We don't want to play passively with c3. We want to strike in the center with c4! } 5... Nf6 { Develop the knight to c3 } { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 6. Nc3 Bb4 { Place the rook on c1 } { [%csl Bc1][%cal Ba1c1] } 7. Rc1 O-O { Kick their bishop away with h3 } { [%csl Bh3][%cal Bh2h3] } 8. h3 Bxf3 { Recapture by queen } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bd1f3] } 9. Qxf3 Ne4 { Develop the bishop to d3 } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 10. Bd3 Nxc3 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb2c3] } 11. bxc3 Ba3 { Now we just play Rb1 and play chess } { [%csl Bb1][%cal Bc1b1] } 12. Rb1 { Play to win and have fun!
--Point--
You want to punish their knight being on c6 so you play c4 to strike in the center instead of play passively with c3. } *


