1... c5 { Pattern #1: Meet c5 with c3 } 2. c3! { The reason why we played c3, is that we support the center, and we are ready to face Qb6 with Qb3. } 2... Qb6 { We are always prepared to meet this with Qb3 } 3. Qb3 { The best move is c4, but let's say that they take our queen } 3... Qxb3 4. axb3 { They just help us because we have control over the semi-open a-file, which we didn't have earlier because our rook was still blocked by our pawn.
--Point--
You want to support the d4 pawn and prepare to meet Qb6 with Qb3. } { [%csl Ga7,Bd2,Yd3][%cal Ga1a7,Bb1d2,Yf1d3] } *


