1... Be7 { Pattern #3: If they are ready to play Nh5 without us having the g5 for the bishop, play h3 (this is an exception to the d5 setups.) } 2. h3! { Now that you played h3, Nh5 is a useless move because we just play Bh2 and keep the bishop. } { [%csl Rf4,Gh2][%cal Rf6h5,Rh5f4,Gf4h2] } 2... O-O { Now we just play Bd3 and play chess } 3. Bd3 { This is normal London System stuff.
--Point--
You want to save your f4 bishop and tuck it in on h2 if it gets attacked. } *


