{ Pattern #4 If their c-pawn is blocked by the knight, strike with c4. }
1. c4! { We don't want to play passively with c3 because they don't have the pawn on c5. } 1... e6 { Our plan is to play Nc3 and Rc1, followed by taking on d5 at the right moment and then playing Nb5. } 2. Nc3 { --Point--
You want to punish them for their knight being on c6 so you play the active c4 instead of c3 which is passive. } { [%csl Bc1,Yd5,Rc7][%cal Ba1c1,Yc4d5,Rc3b5,Rb5c7,Rf4c7,Rc1c7] } *


