[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

1... Bf5 { Pattern #5: Meet Bf5 with c4! } 2. c4! e6 { Now we put pressure on the pawn with Nc3 } 3. Nc3 c6 { They try to solidify the pawn with c6, but now we play Qb3 } 4. Qb3 Qb6 { This is their most common move, but we just play c5 and force them to take. } 5. c5 Qxb3 6. axb3 $16 { Again, we have the open a-file for our rook and we are better in this position.
--Point--
You want to punish them for placing their bishop out into the woods by playing c4 and Qb3 to target the weakness on b7. } *


