1... b6 { Pattern #6: Plant your knight on the e5 square } 2. Ne5! { If they ever take the knight, you take by pawn and gain space on the kingside. For that reason, they will most commonly play Bb7 } 2... Bb7 { Just castle and play f4 on the next move } 3. O-O Qc7 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bf2f4] } 4. f4 { --Point--
You want to place your knight on the strong e5 square followed by attacking on the kingside. } *


