1... e5 { Pattern #8: Meet e5 pawn break with dxc5 (if it has tempo) followed by e4. } 2. dxc5! { We take this pawn so we can play e4 next move! } (2. dxe5 { Do not take this pawn. Take the other one. }) 2... Qxc5 { The reason why we played this is that we wanna play e4! } 3. e4! { This is why we are still slightly better in this position. We are able to break in the center and we have a good position.
--Point--
You want to take on c5 to weaken the pawns a bit, and then you want to play e4 to further weaken their pawns in the center. } *


