{ We start with d4 } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gd2d4] }
1. d4 d5 { Develop the knight to f3 } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 2. Nf3 Nf6 { Place the bishop on f4 } { [%csl Yf4][%cal Yc1f4] } 3. Bf4 e6 { Play e3 } { [%csl Re3][%cal Re2e3] } 4. e3 c5 { Support the pawn with c3 } { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bc2c3] } 5. c3 Nc6 { Develop the knight to d2 } { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bb1d2] } 6. Nbd2 Bd6 { Retreat the bishop to g3 } { [%csl Bg3][%cal Bf4g3] } 7. Bg3 O-O { Develop the bishop to d3 } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 8. Bd3 b6 { This is where the trap starts. We play e4 } { [%csl Be4][%cal Be3e4] } 9. e4 { Their most common move is dxe4 } 9... dxe4 { Recapture by knight } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gd2e4] } 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 Bb7 { Take the pawn on c5 } { [%csl Bc5][%cal Bd4c5] } 12. dxc5 Bxc5 { Attack the knight on c6 with Qa4 } { [%csl Ba4][%cal Bd1a4] } 13. Qa4 Rc8 { Attack the queen with Rd1 } { [%csl Rd1][%cal Ra1d1] } 14. Rd1 Qe8 { This is where the fun starts. We do the greek gift sacrifice with Bxh7+!! } { [%csl Bh7][%cal Be4h7] } 15. Bxh7+!! { Greek Gift Sacrifice!! } 15... Kxh7 { Swing the queen over to Qh4 } { [%csl Bh4][%cal Ba4h4] } 16. Qh4+! { This is the only move! Other moves lose for white. } 16... Kg6 { Now we play Qg5+ } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rh4g5] } 17. Qg5+! Kh7 { Play Qh5+ } { [%csl Rh5][%cal Rg5h5] } 18. Qh5+ Kg8 { Play Ng5 } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rf3g5] } 19. Ng5 Bxf2+ { You can take with either piece and premove Qh7# } { [%csl Rf2][%cal Re1f2] } 20. Kxf2 f6 { Finally, we just mate them on h7. } { [%csl Bh7][%cal Bh5h7] } 21. Qh7# { GG! } *


