{ We play d4 } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 d5 { Play Nf3 } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gg1f3] } 2. Nf3 Nf6 { Play Bf4 } { [%csl Rf4][%cal Rc1f4] } 3. Bf4 e6 { Play e3 } { [%csl Ye3][%cal Ye2e3] } 4. e3 c5 { Support the pawn further with c3 } { [%csl Rc3][%cal Rc2c3] } 5. c3 Nc6 { Develop the knight to d2 } { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bb1d2] } 6. Nbd2 Bd6 { Retreat the bishop to g3 } { [%csl Rg3][%cal Rf4g3] } 7. Bg3 O-O { Develop the bishop to d3 } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 8. Bd3 Qe7 { We play Ne5 } { [%csl Re5][%cal Rf3e5] } 9. Ne5 Nd7 { Take the knight on d7. } { [%csl Rd7][%cal Re5d7] } 10. Nxd7 Bxd7 { This is where the trap starts. Take on d6 } { [%csl Bd6][%cal Bg3d6] } 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 { Now we take the pawn on c5 } { [%csl Bc5][%cal Bd4c5] } 12. dxc5 Qxc5 { Can you find the tactic here in this position? } 13. Bxh7+!! { They need to take } 13... Kxh7 { Check them on h5 } { [%csl Bh5][%cal Bd1h5] } 14. Qh5+ Kg8 { Play Ne4. } { [%csl Re4][%cal Rd2e4] } 15. Ne4 { If they move the queen away, we play Ng5 and it is game over. } 15... g6 { Take the queen } { [%csl Yc5][%cal Ye4c5] } 16. Nxc5 gxh5 { Take the bishop } { [%csl Bd7][%cal Bc5d7] } 17. Nxd7 Rfd8 { Play Nf6+ } { [%csl Rh5][%cal Rd7f6,Rf6h5] } 18. Nf6+ { [%csl Rh5][%cal Rf6h5] } 18... Kf8 { Take the pawn on h5 } { [%csl Rh5][%cal Rf6h5] } 19. Nxh5 $18 { And now it is game over because we have a two pawn advantage. } { [%csl Bg2,Bh2] } *


