{ [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 Nf6 { Develop the bishop to f4 } { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 e6 { Play Nf3 } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 3. Nf3 c5 { We now play e3 } { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 4. e3 Nc6 { And now, the normal move is c3, but we will setup a trap with Nc3 } { [%csl Rc3][%cal Rb1c3] } 5. Nc3!? { The most common move is d5, but it is a blunder because of Nb5! } 5... d5?? { We now play Nb5! } { [%csl Rc7][%cal Bc3b5,Rb5c7,Gf4c7] } 6. Nb5 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gb5c7,Gf4c7] } 6... Qa5+ { Just play c3 } { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bc2c3] } 7. c3 e5 { Just take by knight } { [%csl Ye5][%cal Yf3e5] } 8. Nxe5 { GG! } *


[Event "Master the London System!: Section 3: Trap #5"]
