{ [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 Nf6 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 c5 { Another alternative is to play d5 and gain space in the center. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gd4d5] } 3. d5 { If they play b5, I recommend that you play f3 and e4. If they play Qb6, play Nc3 and we will tackle that on the following chapters. In this chapter, we will learn about what if they play d6. } 3... d6 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 4. Nc3 { We want our knight to be here. } 4... e5 { [%csl Bg5][%cal Bf4g5] } 5. Bg5 Be7 { [%csl Bf6][%cal Bg5f6] } 6. Bxf6 Bxf6 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 7. e4 { We now have our center. } 7... O-O { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 8. Nf3 a6 { [%csl Ba4][%cal Ba2a4] } 9. a4 { We need to prevent them from playing b5 so we play a4. } 9... g6 { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bf3d2] } 10. Nd2 { You have two ideas in mind: Qf3 and Nc4. } 10... Bg7 { [%csl Bc4][%cal Bd2c4] } 11. Nc4 f5 { [%csl Rh4][%cal Rh2h4] } 12. h4 { We do not care about what they are doing over here. Just play h4 and attack. } 12... f4 { Just play h5! } { [%csl Bh5][%cal Bh4h5] } 13. h5 g5 { They try to close it down, but we just play a5! } { [%csl Ba5][%cal Ba4a5] } 14. a5 h6 { [%csl Be2][%cal Bf1e2] } 15. Be2 Qc7 { [%csl Bb6][%cal Bc4b6] } 16. Nb6 Ra7 { [%csl Ba4][%cal Bc3a4] } 17. Nca4 Bd7 { [%csl Bg4][%cal Be2g4] } 18. Bg4 Be8 { [%csl Be6][%cal Bg4e6] } 19. Be6+ Kh8 { [%csl Bg4][%cal Bd1g4] } 20. Qg4 $18 { We are dominating the board and we are now winning.
--Point--
You gain space in the center and you slowly melt them down. } *


