{ [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 Nf6 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 c5 { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bd4d5] } 3. d5 Qb6 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 4. Nc3 { We are gambiting a pawn for the initiative. } 4... Qxb2 { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bf4d2] } 5. Bd2 Qb6 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 6. e4 d6 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bf2f4] } 7. f4 { We need to play aggressively. } 7... e6 { [%csl Bb1][%cal Ba1b1] } 8. Rb1 Qd8 { [%csl Bb5][%cal Bf1b5] } 9. Bb5+ { We are still maintaining the initiative. } 9... Bd7 { [%csl Be6][%cal Bd5e6] } 10. dxe6 fxe6 { [%csl Be5][%cal Be4e5] } 11. e5 dxe5 { [%csl Be5][%cal Bf4e5] } 12. fxe5 Nd5 { [%csl Bg4][%cal Bd1g4] } 13. Qg4 $16 { Any normal move by them will be losing because of how active our pieces are. White is better here.
--Point--
You want to get more active pieces in exchange for a pawn and just start an attack! } *


