1. d4 Nf6 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 e6 { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 3. e3 b6 { We play an interesting move!? Qf3!? } { [%csl Rd1][%cal Bd1f3] } 4. Qf3!? { This is weird because it avoids the normal London System, but this is a very aggressive line to confuse your opponents! You may even catch premovers playing Bb7 once you play this move and you just take the bishop and win! } { [%csl Rf3] } 4... Nc6 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 5. Nc3! { This is the point of our setup! We want to castle queenside. } { [%csl Ra1][%cal Re1a1] } 5... Bb7 { [%csl Bc1][%cal Be1c1] } 6. O-O-O Be7 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be3e4] } 7. e4 O-O { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bd4d5] } 8. d5! { We break through the center and we are already better in this position.
