[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 d5 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 { This is another common move order. White plays this to develop the knight later and develops it after Nd2 and playing the pyramid. } (2. Nf3 { We are studying the 2. Bf4 move order. } { [%csl Gf4,Rf3][%cal Gc1f4,Rg1f3] }) 2... Nf6 { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 3. e3 c5 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bc2c3] } 4. c3 Nc6 { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bb1d2] } 5. Nd2 e6 { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] } 6. Ngf3 { This is the time where we develop the knight. We develop this before the rest. } { [%csl Bf3] } 6... Be7 { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 7. Bd3 { [%csl Rb1,Rg1,Bd4,Be3,Bf2,Bc3,Bb2,Yf1,Yc1,Yf4,Yd3,Rf3,Rd2][%cal Rb1d2,Rg1f3,Bb2d4,Bf2d4,Yf1d3,Yc1f4] } 7... O-O { [%csl Be5][%cal Bf3e5] } 8. Ne5 { We have now completed the London System. We now play chess and just attack!
--Point--
You delay the development of your g1 knight and you develop it after you have completed the pyramid and you have developed the other knight to d2. } { [%csl Bh3,Rh7,Ye5][%cal Bd1f3,Bf3h3,Rh3h7,Rd3h7,Yd4e5] } *


[Event "Master the London System!: Section 5: London vs d5 setups (2. Bf4 instead of 2. Nf3) 2... c5"]
[Date "2026.05.27"]
