{ [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] }
1. d4 Nf6 { [%csl Bf4][%cal Bc1f4] } 2. Bf4 c5 { And here is what I really recommend for those ambitious players. Why not take the pawn? It is just a move that we think it cannot be played but it actually can be played. } 3. dxc5!? { It looks like we are giving up central space, but we are actually preparing to be aggressive. } (3. e3 { Let us tackle the move dxc5 instead since we already tackled this one. }) (3. d5 { This will be tackled later in the study so stay tuned. } 3... b5) 3... Na6 { We now play the sneaky f3!? } 4. f3 { If they take the pawn on c5 right away, we just play e4, Nc3, Qd2 and 0-0-0. Some people will play e6. } 4... e6 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 5. e4 { We now have central space. } 5... Bxc5 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 6. Nc3 Qb6 { Black thinks we are dumb and plays Qb6 attacking the knight and attacking the pawn on b2. Just play Qd2 and ask what they do. } { [%csl Rb2,Rg1][%cal Rb6b2,Bb6g1,Rc5g1] } 7. Qd2!! { We are sacrificing the knight on g1, and I will give you a surprise. } 7... Bxg1?! { Wh' what?? That was just a free knight! What do we do???? The answer is.................... } 8. Rxg1!! { And he sacrificed, THE ROOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOK!!!!!! } 8... Qxg1 { [%csl Bd6][%cal Bf4d6] } 9. Bd6 $18 { Guys, what does black play here? If they play Qb6 we play Nb5 and dominate. If they play b6 we play 0-0-0 and their queen will be trapped. If they do some random move that does nothing we just castle and dominate the whole board.
Guess what, White has a winning advantage!!!!!!!
--Point--
You want to either create a strong attack and castle queenside, or just get into this position where you are down a full rook but their pieces are paralyzed. } (9. O-O-O { This is also a good move. You can see some main lines in the analysis board. } 9... Qb6 10. Bd6! { Preventing the castle... } { [%cal Gf4d6,Rd6f8,Rd6b8] } 10... h6 { I guess a good way to do here is to control the c7-square! Therefore, Nb5 can be good! } { [%csl Gc7] } 11. Nb5 { [%csl Rc7][%cal Rb5c7] } 11... Kd8 { Defensive, huh? } { [%cal Rd8c7] } 12. Na3! { This helps prepare for a great plan, Nc4 and attack the Queen! 👑
Trust, every move leads to Nc4! } { [%csl Rc4,Rb6][%cal Gb5a3,Ra3c4,Rc4b6] }) *


